{"title_page": "Lamprechtshausen", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = Lamprechtshausen\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = \n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = \n| image_shield    = Wappen at lamprechtshausen.png\n| shield_size     = 80x110px\n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = \n| mapsize             = \n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within Salzburg-Umgebung district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|47|58|00|N|12|56|00|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Salzburg (state)|Salzburg]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Salzburg-Umgebung District|Salzburg-Umgebung]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Johann Grie\u00dfner\n| leader_party  = {{Polparty|Austria| \u00d6VP }}\n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 458\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = [[Vehicle registration plates of Austria|SL]]\n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 5112\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 06274\n| website   = [http://www.lamprechtshausen.at www.lamprechtshausen.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''Lamprechtshausen''' is a municipality in the district of [[Salzburg-Umgebung]] in the state of [[Salzburg (state)|Salzburg]] in [[Austria]].\n\n==Geography==\nLamprechtshausen lies in the north of the district of Salzburg-Umgebung in the [[Flachgau]] about 22&nbsp;km north of the city of [[Salzburg]] in the Salzburg Prealps. The municipality is partly flat and partly slightly hilly. It has very little forest.  The municipality of Lamprechtshausen is divided into four [[Cadastral community|cadastral communities]]: Arnsdorf, Lamprechtshausen, Schwerting, and St. Alban.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Cities and towns in Salzburg-Umgebung (district)}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Salzburg-Umgebung District]]\n\n\n{{Salzburg-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = Lamprechtshausen\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = \n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = \n| image_shield    = Wappen at lamprechtshausen.png\n| shield_size     = 80x110px\n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = \n| mapsize             = \n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within Salzburg-Umgebung district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|47|58|00|N|12|56|00|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Salzburg (state)|Salzburg]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Salzburg-Umgebung District|Salzburg-Umgebung]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Johann Grie\u00dfner\n| leader_party  = {{Polparty|Austria| \u00d6VP }}\n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 458\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = [[Vehicle registration plates of Austria|SL]]\n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 5112\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 06274\n| website   = [http://www.lamprechtshausen.at www.lamprechtshausen.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''Lamprechtshausen''' is a municipality in the district of [[Salzburg-Umgebung]] in the state of [[Salzburg (state)|Salzburg]] in [[Austria]].\n\n==Geography==\nLamprechtshausen lies in the north of the district of Salzburg-Umgebung in the [[Flachgau]] about 22 km north of the city of [[Salzburg]] in the Salzburg Prealps. The municipality is partly flat and partly slightly hilly. It has very little forest.  The municipality of Lamprechtshausen is divided into four [[Cadastral community|cadastral communities]]: Arnsdorf, Lamprechtshausen, Schwerting, and St. Alban.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Cities and towns in Salzburg-Umgebung (district)}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Salzburg-Umgebung District]]\n\n{{Salzburg-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lamprechtshausen"}
{"title_page": "Henrik Anker Bjerregaard", "text_new": "[[File:Henrik Anker Bjerregaard OB.00109.jpg|thumb|Henrik Anker Bjerregaard painted by [[Jacob Munch]].]]\n'''Henrik Anker Bjerregaard''' (1 January 1792 \u2013 7 April 1842) was a Norwegian poet, dramatist and judge.\n\nBorn in [[Ringsaker]],<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007 |title=Bjerregaard, Henrik Anker |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location= |url=http://www.snl.no/article.html?id=469756 }}{{dead link|date=March 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> he grew up in [[V\u00e5g\u00e5]] from the age of eight. He studied at the [[University of Copenhagen]], but returned to Norway in 1814<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kloken.no/litteratur/forfatter.asp?ID=4|title=Henrik Anker Bjerregaard (1792\u20131842)|last=L\u00f8ken|first=Knut-Anders|language=Norwegian|accessdate=22 December 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070704133440/http://kloken.no/litteratur/forfatter.asp?ID=4 |archivedate=2007-07-04}}</ref> and graduated from the [[University of Oslo|Royal Frederick University]] with the [[cand.jur.]] degree in 1815. He climbed the career ladder as a jurist, was a solicitor and chief justice in the [[diocese of Oslo|diocesan]] court of [[Oslo|Christiania]] before being appointed as a [[Supreme Court of Norway|Supreme Court]] [[Assessor (law)|Assessor]] in 1830.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |year=1915 |title=Bjerregaard, Henrik Anker |encyclopedia=Salmonsens Konversations Leksikon |publisher=J. H. Schultz |location=Copenhagen |url=http://runeberg.org/salmonsen/2/3/0372.html }}</ref> He remained in this position until his death.\n\nBjerregaard was also a prominent lyricist. Together with [[Conrad Nicolai Schwach]] and [[Maurits Hansen]] he was among the most important lyricists after [[Norway in 1814|Norway's independence in 1814]], in the generation before [[Henrik Wergeland]] and [[Johan Sebastian Welhaven]].<ref name=dagb>{{cite news|url=http://www.dagbladet.no/kronikker/960623-kro-1.html |title=Litter\u00e6r klikk i 1820-\u00e5rene |last=Stubhaug |first=Arild |date=23 June 1996 |work=Dagbladet |language=Norwegian |accessdate=22 December 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605044633/http://www.dagbladet.no/kronikker/960623-kro-1.html |archivedate=5 June 2011 }}</ref><ref name=grave>{{cite web|url=http://www.gravferdsetaten.oslo.kommune.no/getfile.php/Gravferdsetaten/Internett/Dokumenter/dokument/sentralt/gravlundsboken.pdf|title=Her hviler.... Kjente personer p\u00e5 kirkeg\u00e5rdene i Oslo sentrum|last=Haaland|first=\u00d8yvind|author2=Mellum, Mari|date=1999|publisher=Oslo municipality|language=Norwegian|accessdate=17 December 2008}}</ref> According to the [[1911 Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica|1911 ''Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica'']], Bjerregaard had a \"varied talent\", and his body of work contains \"some charming studies from nature, and admirable patriotic songs\".<ref name=eb1911>{{cite EB1911 |wstitle=Norway#Literature |display=Norway \u00a7 Literature |volume=19|page=816 |first=Edmund |last=Gosse |authorlink=Edmund Gosse}}</ref> In 1820, Bjerregaard had entered a contest to write the new [[national anthem of Norway]], and his hymn ''[[S\u00f8nner av Norge|S\u00f8nner af Norge]]'', melody written by [[Christian Blom]], was selected as the winner.<ref name=snl/> The song stood as the national anthem of Norway until 1864, when ''[[Ja, vi elsker dette landet]]'' was written. Bjerregaard also wrote plays, including ''Fjeldeventyret'' (1825) and ''Magnus Barfods S\u00f8nner'' (1830), and was a theatre critic. However, he largely ceased his literary production after his 1830 appointment as Supreme Court Assessor.<ref name=snl/>\n\nBjerregaard was married to actress Henriette Hansen, who was several years his junior.<ref name=dagb/> He died on April 7, 1842, aged 50, and was buried at [[V\u00e5r Frelsers gravlund]].<ref name=grave/> The road ''Bjerregaards vei'' in Oslo has been named after him.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.nb.no/nbsok/search?action=search&mediatype=b\u00f8ker&format=Digitalt%20tilgjengelig&searchString=creator:%22bjerregaard,henrik%20anker%22 Digitized books by Bjerregaard] in the [[National Library of Norway]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bjerregaard, Henrik Anker}}\n[[Category:1792 births]]\n[[Category:1842 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Norwegian poets]]\n[[Category:Norwegian male poets]]\n[[Category:Norwegian theatre critics]]\n[[Category:National anthem writers]]\n[[Category:University of Oslo alumni]]\n[[Category:Supreme Court of Norway justices]]\n[[Category:Norwegian male dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:19th-century Norwegian dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:19th-century Norwegian male writers]]\n[[Category:Burials at V\u00e5r Frelsers gravlund]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Henrik Anker Bjerregaard OB.00109.jpg|thumb|Henrik Anker Bjerregaard painted by [[Jacob Munch]].]]\n'''Henrik Anker Bjerregaard''' (1 January 1792 \u2013 7 April 1842) was a Norwegian poet, dramatist and judge.\n\nBorn in [[Ringsaker]],<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007 |title=Bjerregaard, Henrik Anker |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location= |url=http://www.snl.no/article.html?id=469756 }}{{dead link|date=March 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> he grew up in [[V\u00e5g\u00e5]] from the age of eight. He studied at the [[University of Copenhagen]], but returned to Norway in 1814<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kloken.no/litteratur/forfatter.asp?ID=4|title=Henrik Anker Bjerregaard (1792\u20131842)|last=L\u00f8ken|first=Knut-Anders|language=Norwegian|accessdate=22 December 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070704133440/http://kloken.no/litteratur/forfatter.asp?ID=4 |archivedate=2007-07-04}}</ref> and graduated from the [[University of Oslo|Royal Frederick University]] with the [[cand.jur.]] degree in 1815. He climbed the career ladder as a jurist, was a solicitor and chief justice in the [[diocese of Oslo|diocesan]] court of [[Oslo|Christiania]] before being appointed as a [[Supreme Court of Norway|Supreme Court]] [[Assessor (law)|Assessor]] in 1830.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |year=1915 |title=Bjerregaard, Henrik Anker |encyclopedia=Salmonsens Konversations Leksikon |publisher=J. H. Schultz |location=Copenhagen |url=http://runeberg.org/salmonsen/2/3/0372.html }}</ref> He remained in this position until his death.\n\nBjerregaard was also a prominent lyricist. Together with [[Conrad Nicolai Schwach]] and [[Maurits Hansen]] he was among the most important lyricists after [[Norway in 1814|Norway's independence in 1814]], in the generation before [[Henrik Wergeland]] and [[Johan Sebastian Welhaven]].<ref name=dagb>{{cite news|url=http://www.dagbladet.no/kronikker/960623-kro-1.html |title=Litter\u00e6r klikk i 1820-\u00e5rene |last=Stubhaug |first=Arild |date=23 June 1996 |work=Dagbladet |language=Norwegian |accessdate=22 December 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605044633/http://www.dagbladet.no/kronikker/960623-kro-1.html |archivedate=5 June 2011 }}</ref><ref name=grave>{{cite web|url=http://www.gravferdsetaten.oslo.kommune.no/getfile.php/Gravferdsetaten/Internett/Dokumenter/dokument/sentralt/gravlundsboken.pdf|title=Her hviler.... Kjente personer p\u00e5 kirkeg\u00e5rdene i Oslo sentrum|last=Haaland|first=\u00d8yvind|author2=Mellum, Mari|date=1999|publisher=Oslo municipality|language=Norwegian|accessdate=17 December 2008}}</ref> According to the [[1911 Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica|1911 ''Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica'']], Bjerregaard had a \"varied talent\", and his body of work contains \"some charming studies from nature, and admirable patriotic songs\".<ref name=eb1911>{{cite EB1911 |wstitle=Norway#Literature |display=Norway \u00a7 Literature |volume=19|page=816 |first=Edmund |last=Gosse |authorlink=Edmund Gosse}}</ref> In 1820, Bjerregaard had entered a contest to write the new [[national anthem of Norway]], and his hymn ''[[S\u00f8nner av Norge|S\u00f8nner af Norge]]'', melody written by [[Christian Blom]], was selected as the winner.<ref name=snl/> The song stood as the national anthem of Norway until 1864, when ''[[Ja, vi elsker dette landet]]'' was written. Bjerregaard also wrote plays, including ''Fjeldeventyret'' (1825) and ''Magnus Barfods S\u00f8nner'' (1830), and was a theatre critic. However, he largely ceased his literary production after his 1830 appointment as Supreme Court Assessor.<ref name=snl/>\n\nBjerregaard was married to actress Henriette Hansen, who was several years his junior.<ref name=dagb/> He died on April 7, 1842, aged 50, and was buried at [[V\u00e5r Frelsers gravlund]].<ref name=grave/> The road ''Bjerregaards vei'' in Oslo has been named after him.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.nb.no/nbsok/search?action=search&mediatype=b\u00f8ker&format=Digitalt%20tilgjengelig&searchString=creator:%22bjerregaard,henrik%20anker%22 Digitized books by Bjerregaard] in the [[National Library of Norway]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bjerregaard, Henrik Anker}}\n[[Category:1792 births]]\n[[Category:1842 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Norwegian poets]]\n[[Category:Norwegian male poets]]\n[[Category:Norwegian dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Norwegian theatre critics]]\n[[Category:National anthem writers]]\n[[Category:University of Oslo alumni]]\n[[Category:Supreme Court of Norway justices]]\n[[Category:Norwegian male dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:19th-century Norwegian dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:19th-century Norwegian male writers]]\n[[Category:Burials at V\u00e5r Frelsers gravlund]]\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:duplicate categorization; already in subcat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henrik_Anker_Bjerregaard"}
